{%- comment -%}
  ASR Outdoor — Visible UPC/Barcode
  Prints the selected variant's UPC/GTIN as real, crawlable page text (not just
  inside the ld+json script tag). Google's classic web-search indexer weighs
  visible text much more heavily than schema markup for exact-string queries
  like "type a barcode into Google" — Amazon/eBay both print theirs visibly,
  ASR's page currently doesn't. Updates automatically when the shopper changes
  variant, same as price/availability, via Shopify's built-in variant JS.

  HOW TO INSTALL (theme customizer, no code editor needed):
    1. Online Store -> Themes -> Customize.
    2. In the top dropdown, choose "Products" -> "Default product".
    3. In the left "Product information" section, click "Add block".
    4. Choose "Custom liquid".
    5. DRAG the new Custom liquid block so it sits RIGHT BELOW the SKU/price
       area (near where "product-trust-row.liquid" was installed is fine too —
       either position works, this just needs to render on the page).
    6. Paste EVERYTHING in this file into the Custom liquid box.
    7. Save. It now shows on every product automatically.
{%- endcomment -%}

<style>
  .asr-upc-line {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: rgba(var(--color-foreground), 0.75);
    margin: 0.4rem 0;
  }
</style>

<p class="asr-upc-line" data-product-upc>
  {%- if product.selected_or_first_available_variant.barcode != blank -%}
    UPC: {{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.barcode }}
  {%- endif -%}
</p>

<script>
  (function () {
    var el = document.currentScript.previousElementSibling;
    if (!el) return;
    document.addEventListener('variant:change', function (evt) {
      var variant = evt.detail && evt.detail.variant;
      if (!variant) return;
      el.textContent = variant.barcode ? ('UPC: ' + variant.barcode) : '';
    });
  })();
</script>
